  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nAs pointed out by @xAlisher in recent internal discussions, the new UI components are previewed in a smaller _viewport width_ than what's in Figma. This creates friction for designers to review components because they have to scale images, and thus have a hard time seeing if they perfectly match with what's in Figma.\r\n\r\nBelow is a screenshot of one of @xAlisher's analysis:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"600\" alt=\"Screenshot_2022-09-01_at_15 14 30\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46027/187914417-062a8e1b-faa0-4676-833e-2cf09b379157.png\">\r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\nMake the preview area of the component occupy the full width available.\r\n",
